rmation about the Romantic era and its major figures-Wordsworth, Keats, and Coleridge. The publication of unexpurgated and authoritative texts is an important literary event.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAuthors, Englishy19th centuryvCorrespondence. 4aLiterary Studies.1 aLamb, Mary Anne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMarrs, Edwin W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172751140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501727511423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501727511/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles